# =============================================================================
# DISPOSABLE / DEBUG — Step-3.7-Flash-NVFP4 dual DGX Spark GB10 TP=2
#
# Variant: "ep-off-ray-tuned-kv8g-debug" — Attempt 12A: FIXED KV CACHE SIZE
# (8GiB) ON TOP OF ATTEMPT 11A's EP-OFF + RAY-TUNED CONFIG
#
# Purpose (see docs/diagnostics/dgx-spark-uma-memory-freeze.md, "Attempt 12"):
# Attempt 11A (EP off, GPU_MEMORY_UTILIZATION=0.85) reached a clean serving
# state (Application startup complete, no Ray OOM, no host freeze) but
# spark01/head MemAvailable still dropped ~38GB (51.9GB -> 13.86GB) during
# the ~6-minute window between weight-loading completion and serving
# readiness, overlapping the "Available KV cache memory" / "GPU KV cache
# size" log lines (15:05:08-15:06:07 UTC) and engine startup
# (-> 15:09:00 UTC "Application startup complete"). This run tests whether
# directly fixing KV cache memory to 8GiB via `--kv-cache-memory-bytes`
# (instead of letting vLLM derive KV cache size from
# GPU_MEMORY_UTILIZATION=0.85's leftover headroom) changes the magnitude or
# timing of this decline.
#
# This is IDENTICAL to .env.step37-fi-aot-tp2-ep-off-ray-tuned-debug
# (Attempt 11A) except for one added arg:
#
#   --kv-cache-memory-bytes 8589934592   (= 8 GiB = 8 * 1024^3 bytes)
#
# NOTE on GPU_MEMORY_UTILIZATION: kept at 0.85 (unchanged from Attempt 11A)
# for continuity, but per `vllm serve --help=CacheConfig`:
#   "kv_cache_memory_bytes (when not-None) ignores gpu_memory_utilization"
# -- i.e. with --kv-cache-memory-bytes set, GPU_MEMORY_UTILIZATION no longer
# controls KV-cache sizing specifically. It may still influence other
# memory-profiling paths (non-KV activation/workspace memory), so it is left
# unchanged rather than removed, to keep this a single-variable change vs.
# Attempt 11A (KV-cache sizing method: derived -> fixed).
#
# Unchanged from Attempt 11A:
#   - EP disabled (--enable-expert-parallel NOT present)
#   - --enforce-eager retained
#   - MAX_MODEL_LEN=8192 / MAX_NUM_SEQS=4 / MAX_NUM_BATCHED_TOKENS=8192
#   - Ray safety-net knobs (RAY_INCLUDE_DASHBOARD=false,
#     RAY_OBJECT_STORE_MEMORY_BYTES=4294967296,
#     RAY_memory_usage_threshold=0.90, RAY_memory_monitor_refresh_ms=100,
#     RAY_DASHBOARD_MAX_EVENTS_TO_CACHE=1000)
#
# Interpretation:
#   - If the ~38GB head-node decline shrinks or disappears with a fixed
#     8GiB KV cache -> KV cache size calculation/allocation (the "Available
#     KV cache memory" / "GPU KV cache size" determination step) is
#     implicated as a major contributor.
#   - If the ~38GB decline persists essentially unchanged -> the decline is
#     not primarily driven by KV-cache sizing itself; more likely engine
#     startup / CUDA UVM virtual-memory mapping behavior / rank0-specific
#     RayWorkerWrapper allocation (independent of how KV cache size is
#     computed).
#   - 8GiB was chosen as a deliberately small, fixed value (vs. Attempt
#     11A's derived "GPU KV cache size: 790,438 tokens" / "Available KV
#     cache memory: 37.8 GiB") to maximize contrast if KV-cache sizing is
#     the driver.
#
# DO NOT promote this file to a stable preset. Run only with
# scripts/diag/trace-memory.sh (with sudo, for proc_maps/smaps capture) and
# scripts/diag/memory-guard.sh active on BOTH nodes, per the runbook. Reboot
# both nodes before this run.
# =============================================================================

# ---- Image ----
VLLM_IMAGE=vllm-spark:v022-d568-ngc2605-tx5102-vllm022-step3p7
ENTRYPOINT_FILE=./entrypoints/entrypoint.sh

# ---- Model ----
MODEL_PATH=/home/bjk110/Documents/Models/stepfun-ai/Step-3.7-Flash-NVFP4
MODEL_CONTAINER_PATH=/models/Step-3.7-Flash-NVFP4
SERVED_MODEL_NAME=stepfun-ai/Step-3.7-Flash-NVFP4

# ---- Cluster ----
CLUSTER_MODE=dual-rdma
TP_SIZE=2
HEAD_ROCE_IP=10.10.10.1
WORKER_ROCE_IP=10.10.10.2
ROCE_IF_NAME=enp1s0f0np0
IB_HCA_NAME=rocep1s0f0
RAY_PORT=6379
DISTRIBUTED_BACKEND=ray

# ---- vLLM Serving (unchanged from Attempt 11A) ----
HOST_PORT=8000
MAX_MODEL_LEN=8192
MAX_NUM_SEQS=4
GPU_MEMORY_UTILIZATION=0.85
MAX_NUM_BATCHED_TOKENS=8192

# ---- Extra args ----
# --enable-expert-parallel REMOVED (same as Attempt 11A). Added vs. Attempt
# 11A: --kv-cache-memory-bytes 8589934592 (8 GiB fixed KV cache).
VLLM_EXTRA_ARGS=--trust-remote-code --quantization modelopt --kv-cache-dtype fp8 --kv-cache-memory-bytes 8589934592 --no-enable-flashinfer-autotune --reasoning-parser step3p5 --enable-auto-tool-choice --tool-call-parser step3p5 --enforce-eager

# ---- Runtime env ----
PYTORCH_CUDA_ALLOC_CONF=expandable_segments:True
NCCL_IB_DISABLE=0
NCCL_DEBUG=WARN
NCCL_NVLS_ENABLE=0
NCCL_NET=Socket

# ---- Patch toggles ----
APPLY_TEXT_ONLY_SHIM=0
VLLM_USE_BREAKABLE_CUDAGRAPH=0
VLLM_MEMORY_PROFILER_ESTIMATE_CUDAGRAPHS=1

# ---- NGC 26.05 specifics ----
FLASHINFER_CUDA_ARCH_LIST=12.1
VLLM_USE_RAY_V2_EXECUTOR_BACKEND=0
VLLM_NCCL_SO_PATH=/usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu/libnccl.so.2

# ---- NVFP4 model-specific ----
VLLM_MARLIN_USE_ATOMIC_ADD=0
VLLM_USE_FLASHINFER_MOE_FP4=0
VLLM_NVFP4_GEMM_BACKEND=cutlass

# ---- Ray tuning knobs (ACTIVE for this experiment, same values as
#      Attempt 11A -- see docker-compose.yml for the env passthroughs) ----
RAY_INCLUDE_DASHBOARD=false
RAY_OBJECT_STORE_MEMORY_BYTES=4294967296
RAY_memory_usage_threshold=0.90
RAY_memory_monitor_refresh_ms=100
RAY_DASHBOARD_MAX_EVENTS_TO_CACHE=1000
